description:
Order No. РД-01-1031 dated 15.12.2021 to approve the samples for a digital COVID certificate for vaccination against COVID-19 for an administered booster dose (revaccination) in Bulgaria: 
a) Digital EU COVID certificate (EU DIGITAL COVID CERTIFICATE) for a booster dose administered after a completed vaccination course with a single-dose vaccine, according to Appendix No. 1;
b) Digital EU COVID certificate (EU DIGITAL COVID CERTIFICATE) for a booster dose administered after a completed vaccination course with a two-dose vaccine, according to Appendix No. 2.

As of 17 March 2020, the movement of all international trains through the border crossings on the territory of Bulgaria will be stopped. International trains that will not run are:
• International express trains № 7990 / № 7991 Sofia-Belgrade-Sofia;
• International fast trains № 1090 / № 1091 Vidin-Craiova-Vidin;
• International fast trains № 361 / № 360 Sofia-Thessaloniki-Sofia, which retain their movement on the territory of the country in the section Sofia-Kulata-Sofia;
• International express trains № 462 / № 463 Sofia-Bucharest-Sofia, which retain their movement on the territory of the country in the section Sofia-Ruse-Sofia;
• International fast trains № 493 / № 492 Sofia-Istanbul-Sofia, which retain their movement on the territory of the country in the section Sofia-Svilengrad-Sofia."

Effective 27/03/2020, Bulgaria:The following confirmed cases of COVID-19 are subject to mandatory home isolation (quarantine) and treatment for a period of 28 days from the date of the confirmatory laboratory test:
a ) asymptomatic persons (discovered as contacts or in the course of conducted epidemiological studies);
b) individuals with mild clinical complaints (body temperature < 380C, cough, malaise, runny nose, sore throat, gastrointestinal symptoms, such as nausea, vomiting and/or diarrhea, without changes in mental status (ie, confusion or lethargy) and without accompanying chronic diseases or immunocompromising conditions, etc.
